      },
      {
        "id": "_context",
        "title": "Context",
        "level": 2,
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "html": "Il progetto Magrathea ObjectStore implementa un AWS S3-compatible object storage con Spring Boot 4 WebFlux. La struttura modulare deve separare rigorosamente il dominio puro (DDD) dall&#039;infrastruttura reattiva, seguendo i pattern definiti dagli agenti <code>domain-coder</code> e <code>app-infra-coder</code>."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "_decision",
        "title": "Decision",
        "level": 2,
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "html": "Ogni bounded context e&#039; suddiviso in tre moduli Maven flat sibling:"
          },
          {
            "type": "section",
            "id": "_1_boundedn_domain_dominio_puro_ddd",
            "title": "1. `<boundedN>-domain` — Dominio puro (DDD)",
            "level": 3,
            "blocks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "ulist",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "Java 17+ records per aggregate root (Bucket, S3Object)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Value objects come record immutabili (ObjectKey, Region, StorageClass)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Domain events con sealed interface",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Repository interfaces con <code>CompletableFuture</code> (standard Java async)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Domain services con logica business pura",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "<code>BinaryContent</code> value object: SOLO metadati (content-type, filename, size, compression, checksum)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "<strong>NO byte[]</strong>, NO DataBuffer, NO Spring imports, NO JPA, NO reactive types",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Test: JUnit puro, zero Spring context",
                "blocks": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "section",
            "id": "_2_boundedn_application_orchestrazione_applicativa",
            "title": "2. `<boundedN>-application` — Orchestrazione applicativa",
            "level": 3,
            "blocks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "ulist",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "Application services con <code>@Service</code>",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "DTO come Java records (CreateBucketCommand, PutObjectCommand, BucketResponse, ObjectResponse)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Bridge tra CompletableFuture (dominio) e Mono/Flux (infrastruttura)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "CAN dipendere da Spring",
                "blocks": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "section",
            "id": "_3_boundedn_infrastructure_adapter_reattivi",
            "title": "3. `<boundedN>-infrastructure` — Adapter reattivi",
            "level": 3,
            "blocks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "ulist",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "<strong>RouterFunction<ServerResponse></strong> per tutti gli endpoint HTTP (NO @Controller, NO @RequestMapping)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "XML serializzato con <code>@JacksonXmlRootElement</code> record (NO StringBuilder)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "<code>BinaryContentAdapter</code>: BinaryContent (metadati) ↔ DataBuffer/Flux<DataBuffer> (bytes)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Content store per binary data (ConcurrentHashMap + file persistence)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Persistenza su file single-node con DataBuffer (NO R2DBC)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Test: Cucumber BDD con WebTestClient + AWS CLI verification",
                "blocks": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "section",
            "id": "_4_moduli_aggiuntivi",
            "title": "4. Moduli aggiuntivi",
            "level": 3,
            "blocks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "ulist",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "<code>shared-domain</code>: BinaryContent (cross-cutting)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "<code>bootstrap-application</code>: Spring Boot entry point, compone i moduli attivi",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "<code>persistence-context-*</code>: placeholder vuoti (non implementati in v1)",
                "blocks": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "_conseguenze",
        "title": "Conseguenze",
        "level": 2,
        "blocks": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "html": "<strong>Positive</strong>:"
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "ulist",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "Dominio puramente business, testabile senza Spring",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Framework e reactive types confinati all&#039;infrastruttura",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "RouterFunction permette routing S3-compatible preciso (XML vs JSON content negotiation)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "DDD garantisce che il modello riflette le specifiche AWS S3 reali",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Spring Reactive (WebFlux, DataBuffer, Flux/Mono) e&#039; gestito interamente in infrastruttura",
                "blocks": []
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "html": "<strong>Negative</strong>:"
          },
          {
            "type": "list",
            "style": "ulist",
            "items": [
              {
                "text": "9 moduli da gestire (6 attivi + 3 placeholder)",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "Mapping layer tra dominio e persistence",
                "blocks": []
              },
              {
                "text": "No Spring DI nel dominio",
                "blocks": []
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": "_related_adrs",
        "title": "Related ADRs",
